name: Augustine BRIMBAU v. AUSDALE EQUIPMENT RENTAL CORPORATION
name_abbreviation: Brimbau v. Ausdale Equipment Rental Corp.

parties: Augustine BRIMBAU v. AUSDALE EQUIPMENT RENTAL CORPORATION.

opinions.text:
ORDER
The defendant’s motion for extension of the time within which to file its brief to February 29, 1980 is granted. The defendant’s motion for permission to file a brief in excess of 50 pages is granted, provided, that said brief shall not exceed 65 pages.
DORIS, J., did not participate.

attorneys: Raymond A. LaFazia, Joseph A. Kelly, Providence, for plaintiff.
Higgins, Cavanagh & Cooney, Kenneth P. Borden, Providence, for defendant.

Augustine BRIMBAU v. AUSDALE EQUIPMENT RENTAL CORPORATION.
No. 79-401-A.

Feb. 21, 1980.

Higgins, Cavanagh & Cooney, Kenneth P. Borden, Providence, for defendant.
